description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An opportunity has arisen for the position of full time Clinical Lead Nurse within Mental Health Older Persons Services at Wold View organic inpatient service. The post holder will work as part of the multi-disciplinary team delivering high quality, patient focused care in collaboration with family and in conjunction with partnership working. This post is on an 18 bedded mixed gender ward at the newly commissioned Foss Park Hospital in York. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an exciting and challenging role and will afford the opportunity to work as part of a supportive team that is focused on delivering high standards of care through evidenced based practice. As a Band 6 Nurse, you will work closely with patients and their relatives/ carers as part of a multi-disciplinary team to help plan, develop and implement behaviour support plans within a well-being focused model of working. You will also support and supervise staff within the multi-disciplinary team&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;. Experience of &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;working in a multidisciplinary mental health setting &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;is&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; required for this post. We are looking for someone who is motivated, enthusiastic and compassionate about improving the lives of those with dementia.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be required to work a shift pattern that will compromise working across a 24/7 rota. The post holder will need to be flexible, adaptable and with the ability to work on their own initiative and be able to communicate with all agencies relevant to patient care. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Neil McAdam, Locality Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;neil.mcadam@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;07949693982&lt;/p&gt;
